Re: Version 0.3.18

Bitcointalk

2010-12-09 15:17:53 UTC - [11]Original Post

   I came to agree with Gavin about whitelisting when I realized how
   quickly new transaction types can be added.
   [12]Quote from: nanotube on December 09, 2010, 06:19:05 AM
   why not make it easier on everyone and just allow say, 64 or 128 bytes
   of random data in a transaction?
   Thatʼs already possible.  <pubkey> OP_CHECKSIG.  <pubkey> can be 33 to
   120 bytes.
   I also support a third transaction type for timestamp hash sized
   arbitrary data.  Thereʼs no point not having one since you can already
   do it anyway.  It would tell nodes they donʼt need to bother to index
   it.
